<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839883>
    dc:description "Fig. 12. Calcideletrix breviramosa Mägdefrau, 1937. A–C. Holotype covering several square centimetres of an Upper Cretaceous belemnite from Misburg, Germany. Close-up in B shows main tunnels with lateral secondary galleries and close-up in C illustrates connections to the substrate surface at the end of the secondary branches (arrows)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3839883/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

